Frequently Asked Questions
--------------------------

1. LinkageError/UnsupportedClassVersionError exception on run

Your JVM is too old to run the application, see "Running" section on README.

2. Can't connect from other machines, only localhost works

Program uses port 4000 for client connections. On some systems (e.g.: Windows)
this port can be blocked for non-localhost connections, and you may need to add
the java binary to the applications allowed to bypass firewall rules.

3. Typing numbers in telnet is too boring

If you have bash and awk you can use the nrccClient.sh file available in
the scripts directory to send random numbers to the server.